Algiers - An Algerian military plane
crashed near an airport outside the capital Algiers, killing
several people on Wednesday, local media and a witness said. More than 100 military personnel were on board the plane
when it came down near Boufarik airport, local channel Ennahar
TV reported. There was no immediate confirmation from
authorities. Television footage showed black smoke billowing near a
motorway and a crowd of security officials and others standing
in a field next to the crash site.   The tail fin of a plane could be seen above olive trees,
with smoke and flames rising from the wreckage. Reuters